The new Mr South Africa 2020's nameÂ is Hannes Van Der Walt and he hails from Kempton Park. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Hannes Van Der Walt has been crowned the new Mr South Africa. Van Der Walt hopes to be a role model for his community. The Kempton Park resident bagged the title during a virtual ceremony, held on Saturday. He said he was inspired to take part in the competition to inspire others. "The Mr South Africa brand is one I admired and Henrich Gabler's year of reigning inspired me to go out and inspire others as well," Van Der Walt said. Due to COVID-19, the event was live-streamed online to a global audience. The event was judge by Aretha Bauwens, Saskia Riley and Storm Johnson. Watch the interview above for more